    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to any scripts written with a running hand, so that the characters are rapidly formed by raising the pen very little, and in consequence characters have rounded angles and become slanted, and letters or strokes are often combined in a continuous stroke (a ligature).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
